1.AIM:
            To design a java package shapes containing classes circle , rectangle and square.

2.ALGORITHM:
	Create a package named shapes
	Inside the package:
•	Define a circle class with radius as data and methods to compute area & perimeter
•	Define a rectangle class with length and breadth as data and methods to compute area & perimeter
•	Define a square class with side as data and methods to compute area & perimeter
	In another program (outside the package), import the package shapes
	Create objects of circle , rectangle and square
	Call their methods to display area and perimeter





3.JAVA CODE:
 import java.util.*;
class Circle {
private double radius;
public Circle(double radius) {
 this.radius = radius;
    }
 public double area() {
 return Math.PI * radius * radius;
    }
public double perimeter() {
        return 2 * Math.PI * radius;
    }
}
class Rectangle {
    private double length, breadth;
public Rectangle(double length, double breadth) {
        this.length = length;
        this.breadth = breadth;
    }
public double area() {
        return length * breadth;
    }
 public double perimeter() {
        return 2 * (length + breadth);
    }
}
class Square {
    private double side;
 public Square(double side) {
        this.side = side;
    }
 public double area() {
        return side * side;
    }
 public double perimeter() {
        return 4 * side;
    }
}
public class ShapesDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Circle c = new Circle(5);
        Rectangle r = new Rectangle(4, 6);
        Square s = new Square(4);
System.out.println("Circle: Area = " + c.area() + ", Perimeter = " + c.perimeter());
System.out.println("Rectangle: Area = " + r.area() + ", Perimeter = " + r.perimeter());
System.out.println("Square: Area = " + s.area() + ", Perimeter = " + s.perimeter());
    }
    }

4.OUTPUT:
Circle: Area = 78.53981633974483, Perimeter = 31.41592653589793
Rectangle: Area = 24.0, Perimeter = 20.0
Square: Area = 16.0, Perimeter = 16.0
